  60:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****               The dynamic linked-list format refer to the customized linked-list node where only DM
  61:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****               parameters are fetched and executed (Example: data size = 20 on previous node, and da
  62:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****               current node => No need to update it).
  63:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_dma_ex.c **** 
  64:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****       For linked-list transfers, the DMA channel can execute the linked-list queue node by node. Th
  65:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****       link step mode. When activated, enabling the DMA channel first time allows to fetch the head 
  66:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****       then it stops. Then, another DMA channel enable is needed to execute the node. After that, ke
  67:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****       DMA channel is needed to execute each node until the end of linked-list queue. When the linke
  68:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****       circular, enabling the DMA channel in an infinite loop is required to keep the DMA channel ru
  69:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****       is useful for debug purpose or asynchronously executing queue nodes.
